---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About First7">

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6">

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">About First7</h1>

    <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
      First7 is built to help you develop a daily habit of faith through Scripture, reflection, and guided plans.
    </p>

    <p>
      In a world full of distractions, it’s easy to lose consistency in your spiritual life. First7 is designed to simplify that — giving you a clear, focused path to spend time with God every day.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-medium">What You’ll Find Here</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)]">
      <li>Simple, structured Bible reading</li>
      <li>Short devotionals for daily reflection</li>
      <li>Guided plans to build consistency</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-medium">Our Goal</h2>

    <p>
      Not to overwhelm you — but to help you start small, stay consistent, and grow deeper in your faith over time.
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">
  About These Teachings
</h2>

<p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
  First7 teachings are designed to encourage spiritual growth through
  Scripture-centered reflection, practical wisdom, prayer, and obedience
  to God. The goal is not merely information, but transformation through
  biblical truth.
</p>

<p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
  Teachings are developed through Scripture study, sermon preparation,
  prayer, biblical research, and spiritual reflection. Many teachings
  synthesize insights learned through pastors, teachers, devotionals,
  and personal study while being carefully rewritten and organized into
  structured formats for clarity and growth.
</p>

<p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
  Unless otherwise noted, Scripture quotations are primarily taken from
  the King James Version (KJV).
</p>

<p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
  Teachings are intentionally concise, structured, and practical. Each
  teaching focuses on biblical truth, insight, application, and prayer
  to help readers grow steadily in faith and discernment.
</p>

<p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
  AI tools may assist with organization, formatting, grammar refinement,
  and content structuring. However, spiritual direction, theological
  emphasis, Scripture selection, and teaching development remain
  human-led and prayerfully guided.
</p>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>